name: Michael Gorelov
headline: Frontend Developer
creator: False
bio:
Hello! My name is Mikhail. I'm a frontend engineer. I have a serious attitude to work and like to get a new knowledge. I had studied on my own, then I was studying in 21School (Ecole 42 franchise). I applied for internship in Sber. I got a job after half a year of internship. In my daily work I use React, TS, Redux, SASS. I've done some interesting things such a HOC for checking users permissions and prevent some actions by them. I've done plenty of tasks with async logic, writing redux modules, functional components and forms.
Also Im building distros on jenkins with parameters and setting them on testing environment
--

Привет!  Меня зовут Михаил. Я трудолюбивый и любознательный фронтенд-реакт разработчик. Обучался самостоятельно, затем поступил в 21School (учился по программе Ecole42) от сбера и через них попал на стажировку в сам сбер. В данный момент работаю в консалтинговой компании Философия.ИТ, входящей в Лигу Цифровой Экономики, на проекте в Сбере. 

На проекте используем стандартный стек для реакта: TS, Redux, SASS. Реализовывал в работе всякие прикольные штуки типа компонентов высшего порядка и множественных асинхронных запросов в цикле, различную хитрую логику древовидных компонентов и тд. Затаскивал в проект MUI, React Hook Form, React Testing Library.  Люблю когда код консистентный и стараюсь писать его качественно и чисто . Рефакторю старый код, когда вижу в этом необходимость. Не боюсь разбираться в легаси, хоть это и бывает больно, выношу из этого уроки как НЕ надо делать. Участвую в код ревью как внутри своей команды, так и в смежных. Есть опыт проведения технических интервью, выступлений с докладами. 

Также в данный момент выполняю роль scrum-мастера и прохожу обучение. Провожу и фасилитирую скрам-события

name: Mohamad Nour Shahin
headline: Software Engineer | Frontend Engineer | Full Stack Engineer  | Researcher @ Innopolis University
creator: False
bio:
Hi there!  👋

I am a dedicated and accomplished Frontend Developer with a profound background in computer science. Currently, I am pursuing my Bachelor of Science in Computer Science at Innopolis University.

💻 With over four years of experience in frontend development, I have mastered a plethora of technologies such as C++, Java, C, Kotlin, React.js, Next.js, Vue.js, and Svelte. At Clivie, I adeptly engineered user interfaces and video editing tools. At ProMed, I spearheaded the frontend development of a dynamic medical course app. At Al-Sahil, I led the creation of a pivotal web application certified by the General Tax Authority of Syria.

🚀 My portfolio includes notable projects like Crown Farms, an e-commerce platform for Dubai-based farms, and InnoSchedule, a sophisticated course schedule management tool for Innopolis University. I have also made significant contributions to the real estate sector with the development of Emkan Properties.

🏆 I am privileged to have received several accolades, including 2nd place in the GoOpenSource hackathon (2024) and the Student of the Year award for scientific activities (2024). Furthermore, I am proud of my publication, "Quantum Microservices: Transforming Software Architecture with Quantum Computing."

🌟 My aspiration is to perpetually innovate and expand the horizons of software development. I am eager to connect with like-minded professionals and explore potential collaborations on groundbreaking projects.

bio:
Frontend Developer | React & TypeScript Expert | Aspiring NEXT.js Specialist | Blockchain Enthusiast

About Me:
I'm a dedicated Frontend Developer with over 4 years of commercial experience in fintech, innovative SAAS application and corporate products. My primary focus is crafting efficient and scalable user interfaces using the React/TypeScript stack, paired with robust state management via Redux or Zustand. Currently, I'm expanding my expertise towards Server-Side Rendering (SSR) with a keen interest in NEXT.js, aiming to deliver high-performance web applications.

Technical Proficiencies:
Languages & Libraries: HTML, CSS, SCSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, React.js, Redux, Zustand, React Query, Next.js, NodeJS, Express, Jest
Tools & Platforms: Git, Webpack, Vite, Storybook, Cypress, i18next
Special Interests: Blockchain technology, Web3 innovations, and decentralized applications (DApps)

Professional Approach:
I tackle projects with utmost responsibility, striving for timely delivery without compromising on quality. Recognized for my team spirit, I’m always keyed into providing results-driven solutions to both team dynamics and business challenges.

Let's Connect:
For collaboration or to discuss the latest in front-end development and blockchain, reach out to me on Telegram: @Khokhlov_P

Mentorship.

Hi, glad to see you here! My name is Aki she/her, a Technical Artist / Graphics Developer,

Whether you need to create a mind-blowing shader, or a unique-looking post-processing effect - I'm here to help! See my website https://akidevcat.github.io/ for more information! And don't miss my works on ArtStation

name: Elisei Smirnov
headline: Innopolis University BS22 | Data Scientist | NLP | QDeep Team | Advanced Engineering School (AES) | VLLM Contributor
creator: False
current_position: ML Engineer (NLP) в Передовой Инженерной Школе
bio:
Я — инженер и исследователь в области искусственного интеллекта и обработки естественного языка. 

Мой профессиональный путь стартовал с призёрства на всероссийском этапе чемпионата WorldSkills 2021, где я занимался разработкой алгоритмов ориентации и стабилизации для спутниковых проектов. Этот опыт стал отправной точкой для развития в IT.

Переход в сферу ИИ открыл передо мной новые горизонты: в 2021 году я собрал команду и стал победителем международного конкурса AIIJC от Сбербанка в треке «Искусственный Интеллект в Медицине». Мы разработали продукт, способный классифицировать COVID-19 поражения на рентгеновских снимках, преодолевая сложности, связанные с некачественными данными, и демонстрируя умение работать на стыке технологий и медицины.

Сегодня я обучаюсь в Университете Иннополис (GPA 4.88), где углубляю знания в высшей математике и IT, а также активно развиваюсь в профессиональной сфере. В настоящее время, работая ML Engineer (NLP) в Передовой Инженерной Школе, я реализую проекты на базе LLM-агентов для автоматизации процессов — от планирования API-вызовов и оптимизации инференса до интеграции с корпоративными сервисами и создания ETL-пайплайнов для образовательного контента.

Мой технический стек включает Python, PyTorch, Hugging Face, VLLM, REST API, Prometheus, Grafana и другие современные инструменты. Опыт full-cycle разработки NLP-решений позволяет мне успешно вести проекты от концепции до масштабируемого MVP, а участие в организации хакатонов и олимпиад подтверждает мои лидерские и коммуникативные навыки.

Помимо технической деятельности, я активно изучаю новые архитектуры LLM-агентов, экспериментирую с оптимизацией инференса (quantization, constrained decoding, speculative decoding) и всегда стремлюсь улучшить уже работающие системы. Мои усилия подкреплены патентами, дипломами международного уровня и сертификатами, подтверждающими профессиональные достижения.

Вне работы я увлекаюсь картингом, лыжами и сноубордом, а также интересуюсь экономикой и маркетингом. Всегда открыт для новых профессиональных контактов и проектов, способствующих росту и развитию в сфере высоких технологий.

name: Sabir Khalitov
headline: Python Software Engineer
creator: False
bio:
Python Backend Engineer, 26 y.o., 6 years in development.

I work with FastAPI, Django, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB. Experienced in web scraping with Selenium, data streaming with Kafka, and background task processing with Redis and Celery. Built data processing pipelines with Airflow and used threading and asyncio to optimize application performance.

I use Docker and Docker Compose for containerized deployments and can set up applications on AWS. I also have experience managing a small team.

I can work with unclear requirements, discussing business needs to define the best technical solution. I’m comfortable working with non-technical stakeholders, translating their needs into well-structured, efficient implementations.

- пакет офис и системы контроля задач (Jira, Trello)

name: Vladislav Kozikov
headline: Producer & Game Designer - Madness Games
creator: False
bio:
Hey, Soul! I'm Vlad. I produce and gamedesign Indi & Mobile games 4+ years

My mission is to create projects that will remain in people's souls for a long time. Create with love something unique from the familiar - both in terms of game design and art-style

My values:
- Uniqueness through a clear niche analysis. Despite the fact that I aim to create a new gaming experience - each project is based on a clear detailed analysis of the niche, projects and audience requests in it. I am ready to consider working on projects outside of this factor, but only if I see potential in them
- The buzz from the projects that I charge my teams with. I appreciate the interests of each person in my projects and am working on it - every person in my teams gets high from what they do
- Emphasis on high-quality TA and the implementation of the result. I work with the documentation very carefully and for each solution I go through a large number of reserches and decompositions
- Continuous improvement of the team and processes. I work with people who are interested in development in their field and set up processes and tasks regarding this

At the moment I am producing Simple Sandbox 3 - the sequel to one of the largest mobile sandboxes. Also, in my free time, I am engaged in pet projects and the development of the gaming community around, helping beginners to start development in gamedev and holding various gamedev events, tournaments and jams.
From additional experience - I participated in a couple of dozen game jams and have gaming experience in many hundreds of completed projects of various genres

headline: COO & Co-Founder at Anything* | Sales & AI

bio:
Hello! I'm Nikita, currently 19 years old. Hailing from Belarus with a passion for technology and entrepreneurship. Presently pursuing my studies in computer science at Innopolis University.

Having gained invaluable experience in managing online stores I began to develop in the field of management. I am now co-founder of a development studio in generative AI and also a startup that will change the interaction between creator and generative AI. 

I had an experience in programming, especially in the Flutter framework, I am adept solutions and develop multiplatform applications for pet-projects.

My fluency in English and Russian helps me to effectively communicate and collaborate across different regions. I thrive in team environments, where I can contribute my expertise in project development and business planning.

Always eager to expand my network and enhance my skill set, I welcome new opportunities for growth and collaboration. Let's connect!

name: Makar Shevchenko
headline: Bachelor student at Innopolis University specializing in Data Analysis and Python development. Participated in a series of academic research and industrial software development. Received awards in hackathons.
creator: False
bio:
Achievments:

Winner of the All-Russian Hackathon “Цифровой Прорыв” with a prize of 1,500,000 rubles (December 2021). Winner of the second and third places (November 2020 and May 2021, respectively) of the same hackathon (https://leadersofdigital.ru)

Diploma of the winner of the All-Russian hackathon “SberCode” 2021 (https://sbercode.tech)

Diploma of the winner of the hackathon “Start. Boo Hackathon 2020, Republic of Tatarstan (http://www.antat.ru/ru/ips/news/10018)

Diploma for the second place in the hackathon “Tender Hack” 2021, Republic of Tatarstan (https://tenderhack.ru)

Diploma of the third degree of the All-Russian Olympiad for schoolchildren "Изумруд" 2020 in the Russian language

Certificates of participation in the hackathons “Цифровой форсаж атомных городов” 2021, “HackAtom” 2021, “Лидеры Цифровой Трансформации” 2020 and in the final stage of the Olympiad for School Students in Informatics from ITMO University

Diplomas of the University for outstanding achievements and contribution to the development of the student community (spring semester 2021, fall semester 2020)


Optional projects:

Implementation of the project “Passcode Data Protection by Using FPGA and Verilog” under supervision of Dr. Artem Burmyakov, Innopolis University. Article on Habr: https://habr.com/en/post/537042/

Development of a hyper-casual mobile game “Throw!” The game is available for download at the following address: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.Syrex.Throw

Main author of the article “Systematic literature review on image-based face recognition methods using deep learning”. The work was carried out under the supervision of Dr. Riby Abraham Boby, Indian Institute of Technology Madras. The work is currently under review in the journal

Development of an Android application for navigating the university and its events, March 2020 (https://github.com/DablSi/Innoapp) 

Developing a web application for collecting student feedback, September 2020 - April 2021 (https://gitlab.com/student-union-it-department)


Extra Professional Training:

Android development course from Tinkoff Fintech, February – May 2021. Topics covered: Kotlin, Android components and lifecycle, View/ViewGroup, RecyclerView, Fragments (https://fintech.tinkoff.ru/study/fintech/android/)


References:

Artem Burmyakov (artem.burmyakov@gmail.com), Assistant Professor, Innopolis University, Russia;
Igor Gaponov (i.gaponov@innopolis.ru), Associate Professor, Innopolis University, Russia.
Riby Abraham Boby (riby.abraham@mytum.de), Professor, Indian Institute of Technology Madras;

name: Georgy Andryushchenko
headline: ML Engineer
creator: False
bio:
I specialize in the effective application of artificial intelligence to text and image processing. My core skills include finding possible approaches to solve a problem, implementing them, and analyzing thier effectiveness. In addition, I develop APIs for implemented approaches and deploy them in production. I also manage development productively using Scrum methodology. I speak excellent English.

I develop machine learning models in Jupyter Notebook using PyTorch, Tensorflow, and sklearn. To work with images and to apply Computer Vision algorithms I use OpenCV. I work with tabular and numerical data in Pandas, numpy and scipy. For visualization I use Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly.

For API development I use Flask or Django. In my work I use PostgreSQL to store and for data storage and manipulation. I use pytest and Postman for testing. I deploy the server with nginx and gunicorn. I know Docker and Hadoop. Freely use Git and Linux.
